# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# NRCC environment contract (canonical, per-stack).
#
# This file is the single source of truth for runtime configuration.
# Every variable listed here is consumed by the nrcc binary
# (Bootstrap layer) or by the Node-RED child process (Runtime layer).
#
# Two layers:
#   1. Bootstrap → fixed at container start; changing requires a restart.
#   2. Runtime   → NODE_RED_* consumed by the ProcessManager on every
#                   Start() of the Node-RED child.
#
# The contract is enforced by TestEnvContract_* in
# internal/service/env_contract_test.go: any os.Getenv call without a
# matching entry here (and vice versa) breaks CI.
#
# Full contract: docs/configuration/env-contract.md
# Per-stack contract (one Compose stack = one Node-RED):
#   docs/adr/0003-docker-first-one-stack-per-node-red.md
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Bootstrap: HTTP + storage (restart required) ─────────────────────────────
# Default: 3001. The HTTP port nrcc serves on. Keep aligned with the
# host port mapping in docker-compose.yml.
PORT=3001
# Default: ./data (container: /data). Where nrcc stores users, sessions,
# JWT secret, backups, env, settings.js.
DATA_DIR=/data

# ── Bootstrap: secrets (restart required) ────────────────────────────────────
# Override via Docker Secrets / file-based input in production.
# See docs/configuration/env-contract.md for the auto-generation fallback.
#
# nrcc rejects three well-known placeholder values to keep insecure
# dev secrets from leaking into production. Pick a real random string.
JWT_SECRET=change-me-in-production
# Encrypts the env-store values written to /data/env.enc. Same
# placeholder rules as JWT_SECRET.
NRCC_ENCRYPTION_KEY=change-me-in-production

# ── Bootstrap: CORS (restart required) ───────────────────────────────────────
# Comma-separated origins the nrcc UI may be loaded from. "*" is
# accepted for development only and emits a startup warning.
NRCC_CORS_ORIGINS=*
# Force "*" regardless of NRCC_CORS_ORIGINS (development only).
# NRCC_CORS_UNSAFE_WILDCARD=false
# Comma-separated CIDR/IP ranges of reverse proxies nrcc should trust
# the X-Forwarded-* headers from. Empty = trust no proxy.
# NRCC_TRUSTED_PROXIES=

# ── Bootstrap: optional behaviour (restart required) ────────────────────────
# Edge mode: resource-safe defaults for Pi/NAS deployments. See ADR 0002.
EDGE_MODE=false
# Disable the bundled Node-RED lifecycle when running NRCC against an
# external Node-RED only. Default true.
# NRCC_MANAGE_NODE_RED=true
# Override the Docker image tag nrcc uses for self-update / external
# Node-RED discovery. Default: the image the running container came from.
# NRCC_IMAGE=
# Backup storage root. Default: $DATA_DIR/backups.
# NRCC_BACKUP_DIR=

# ── Restic (optional, off by default) ────────────────────────────────────────
# Point NRCC at an external restic binary + repository for off-host
# backups. All four vars below must be set together; leave empty to
# disable the feature.
# NRCC_RESTIC_REPO=
# NRCC_RESTIC_BINARY=/usr/bin/restic
# NRCC_RESTIC_PASSWORD=
# NRCC_RESTIC_PASSWORD_FILE=
# NRCC_RESTIC_CACHE_DIR=/tmp/restic-cache

# ── NPM (optional override) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Override the npm binary the Node-RED palette manager invokes. Empty
# = let ProcessManager find it on $PATH.
# NPM_BIN=

# ── Optional: AI assistant (off by default) ──────────────────────────────────
# All five vars below must be set together; leave NRCC_AI_ENABLED=false
# to disable the feature.
# NRCC_AI_ENABLED=false
# NRCC_AI_PROVIDER=openai
# NRCC_AI_ENDPOINT=https://api.openai.com/v1
# NRCC_AI_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini
# NRCC_AI_API_KEY=

# ── Node-RED child runtime (honored by ProcessManager; see #429) ─────────────
# Override the node-red binary path. Default: node-red (resolved on $PATH).
NODE_RED_CMD=node-red
# HTTP port for the Node-RED editor. Default: 1880.
NODE_RED_PORT=1880
# Where Node-RED keeps its userDir (flows, settings.js, node_modules).
# Default: $DATA_DIR. Override to relocate to a separate volume.
# NODE_RED_USER_DIR=/data
# Path to settings.js. Default: $NODE_RED_USER_DIR/settings.js.
# NODE_RED_SETTINGS=/data/settings.js
